title: Validate Print Transaction Behavior with Batching Disabled (The objective of this test is to enhance the throughput time)
custom_preconds:
Feature: Validate Print Transaction Behavior with Batching Disabled

  Scenario: Test print transaction results when batching is disabled
    Given the property "dataservice.gcp.pubsub.batching.enabled" is set to false
    When I execute a Print Transaction
    Then I should run the SQL query "<SELECT 
    CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'TB' AND SEND_PENDING = 'Y') AS send_pending_tb,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'TB' AND SEND_PENDING IS NULL) AS sent_tb,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'PI' AND SEND_PENDING = 'Y') AS send_pending_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'PI' AND SEND_PENDING IS NULL) AS sent_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB') AND SEND_PENDING IS NULL) AS sent_tb_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB') AND SEND_PENDING = 'Y') AS unsent_tb_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB')) AS all_tb_pi  
FROM dual;>"
    And I save the results of the query
    When I update the seventh column using the SQL command "<UPDATE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE 
SET SEND_PENDING = 'Y', send_date = NULL 
WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB');>"
    And I wait for approximately 1 minute
    When I perform a reprint Transaction
    Then I run the same SQL query "<SELECT 
    CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'TB' AND SEND_PENDING = 'Y') AS send_pending_tb,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'TB' AND SEND_PENDING IS NULL) AS sent_tb,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'PI' AND SEND_PENDING = 'Y') AS send_pending_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE = 'PI' AND SEND_PENDING IS NULL) AS sent_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB') AND SEND_PENDING IS NULL) AS sent_tb_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB') AND SEND_PENDING = 'Y') AS unsent_tb_pi,  
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM DATA_BUS_MESSAGE WHERE DATA_BUS_MESSAGE_TYPE_CODE IN ('PI', 'TB')) AS all_tb_pi  
FROM dual;>" again
    And I save the results
    Then I compare the initial result with the reprint result
    And I execute the same steps with the property "dataservice.gcp.pubsub.batching.enabled" set to true
custom_expected:
The Result shows significant improvement when the batching is turned on.
In reference to the steps above the following result have been captured. When batching was enabled, the task took about 183 seconds and sent over 3,000 messages at a speed of around 16.76 messages per second. However, when batching was turned off, the process took much longeralmost 6,907 secondsfor just 12 messages, which is only about 0.0017 messages per second.
